uered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":30,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705197,"age":103,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"William Carnowe was born in 1352, in England. He had at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"1352–":"1352–Surnud","1375–Female":"1375–Surnud","1352–Male":"1352–Surnud","1455":"1455","1375":"1375","1352":"1352","1382":"1382","England":"England"},"fi":{"1352–":"1352–Kuollut","1375–Female":"1375–Kuollut","1352–Male":"1352–Kuollut","1455":"1455","1375":"1375","1352":"1352","1382":"1382","England":"England"},"fr":{"1352–":"1352–Décédé","1375–Female":"1375–Décédée","1352–Male":"1352–Décédé","1455":"1455","1375":"1375","1352":"1352","1382":"1382","England":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"William Carnowe est né en 1352, à Angleterre. Il a eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"1352–":"1352–Ver